    • Method Detail

      • setAsAttrIfNotAfterError

        default void setAsAttrIfNotAfterError(RequestContent content,
                                      java.lang.Object object,
                                      java.lang.String attrName)
        Set object which you want to edit as session attribute in case if it is first Edit...Page loading. In case if it is reloading of this page because of errors in edit form, original object doesn't placed in session (P.S. the Uncompleted...MemoryContainer does but not in this method)
        Parameters:
        content - request content
        object - object that you want to edit
        attrName - attribute's name which will contain your object
